In Alejandro Gonz\xE1lez I\xF1\xE1rritu\u2019s darkly comic film \u201CBirdman,\u201D the lead character\u2014an arrogant actor named Riggan Thomson\u2014is simultaneously tormented by his past success as the superhero Birdman but also driven by the desire for fame again. As a result, he devises a plan to create publicity for his production of The Birdman by playing both roles in the same play and switching back and forth in front of an audience. He also moves into the derelict theater with his daughter where he will perform as part of his preparations on getting back into shape.
